Politics.Headline: Labour Pledges to House 20,000 More Prisoners in Newly Renovated Luxury Cells, While Tories Splurge £730 Million on "Therapeutic" Mental Health Services
Politics.Article: In a bid to outdo each other on tough crime policies, Labour has vowed to build more prison spaces, complete with flat screen TVs and en-suite bathrooms. Meanwhile, the Tories are determined to throw money at mental health services, hoping to pacify the masses with mindfulness and meditation before they inevitably end up behind bars.

General.Article:
"For sale: magic potion guaranteed to bring you success in love, finance, and politics. Results may vary. Proceed with caution.

Seeking roommate with impeccable hygiene, quiet demeanor, and obsession with cleaning. Must also be a pro at cooking and have a trust fund.

Free to a good home: slightly used crystal ball. Predicts future, but only accurately on Thursdays. May also possess mysterious powers of invisibility.

Will trade soul for eternal youth and beauty. Serious inquiries only. Must be willing to sign a legally binding contract in blood.

Lost: pet unicorn named Sparkles. Last seen prancing around the forest with a rainbow-colored mane. Reward offered for safe return."
